  {
   "fieldname": "accounts_intro",
   "fieldtype": "HTML",
   "options": "<div style=\"color:#6c757d;font-size:12px;line-height:1.5;margin:8px 0;\"><p><b>Phase 1 — Setup (one-time per Company, destructive).</b><br>Tick <b>Apply Account Cleanup on Next Sync</b> on the Company Sage Integration row in the Connection tab, then save. The next account-sync run deletes every leaf account on this Company that isn't system-required and isn't already a Sage account, imports all Sage accounts fresh, and flips <b>Setup Complete</b> to true.</p><p><b>Phase 2 — Ongoing (additive, automatic).</b><br>Once Setup Complete is true, the sync only adds new Sage accounts. Nothing is ever deleted or modified.</p><p>System-required accounts (Stock Adjustment, Round Off, Cost of Goods Sold, etc.) are protected — they're never deleted. If Sage has a same-named equivalent it replaces the ERPNext default automatically.</p><p>See the <b>Opening Balances</b> tab to import Sage account opening balances once the account sync is complete.</p></div>"
  },
